    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Short, fluffy fibers obtained from the cylindrical flowers of plants of the genus Typha. Used for filling pillows, upholstery, life jackets, and as sorbents; the fiber provides sound and heat insulation as well as buoyancy.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
